## Dataset Overview

The AI4I Predictive Maintenance Dataset is an industrial machine dataset used to predict machine failures based on sensor and operational data. The dataset contains machine performance measurements collected from a manufacturing environment and is widely used for predictive maintenance projects.

### Dataset Information

| Attribute | Description |
|------------|------------|
| Dataset Name | AI4I Predictive Maintenance Dataset |
| Number of Records | 10,000 |
| Number of Features | 14 |
| Target Variable | Machine Failure |
| Data Type | Structured Tabular Data |

### Features

- UDI (Unique Identifier)
- Product ID
- Type (L, M, H)
- Air Temperature [K]
- Process Temperature [K]
- Rotational Speed [rpm]
- Torque [Nm]
- Tool Wear [min]
- Machine Failure (Target Variable)

### Objective

The objective of this dataset is to develop a machine learning model capable of predicting machine failures before they occur. Early prediction helps reduce downtime, improve maintenance planning, and increase operational efficiency.

### Applications

- Predictive Maintenance
- Failure Detection
- Industrial IoT Analytics
- Machine Health Monitoring
- Manufacturing Optimization
